          text: "Your 'Gāṇḍīva' is your primary skill—your coding ability, your sales pitch, your leadership charm. When you suffer from burnout or a profound loss of purpose (meaning crisis), that skill 'slips from your hand.' You cannot perform at a high level if your 'why' is broken.",
