            text: "In sociology, highly stratified systems (like rigid caste structures) are deeply vulnerable to shocks (like war). Arjuna is rationally identifying that a massive war will break the rigid social code. However, evolutionarily, 'intermingling' and adaptation are often exactly what a stagnant society needs to survive and evolve.",
