        "Arjuna continues his dark prophecy. He believes that the disruption of the family lineage will result in hell (narakāya) for everyone involved. He points to the Vedic ritual of Śrāddha—the offering of rice balls (piṇḍa) and water (udaka) to ancestors. Without pure-blooded descendants to perform these specific rituals accurately, the ancestors will 'fall' from their heavenly realms.",
