            text: "Spiritually, this verse represents the limitation of the Karma Kanda (the ritualistic portion of the Vedas). Krishna will soon tell Arjuna to rise above the three Gunas and the ritualistic promises of the Vedas (Ch 2, V45), pointing him toward actual Self-realization.",
