          text: "We often read self-help books, quote philosophers, and post spiritual quotes on social media ('speaking learned words'). Yet, when someone insults us or a minor tragedy strikes, we lose our minds and fall into anxiety. Krishna’s rebuke applies to us: our vocabulary is enlightened, but our nervous system is still in ignorance.",
