            text: "Rationally, an object is pulled by the strongest gravitational force around it. The senses are massive planets pulling the mind. Willpower is a small asteroid trying to pull it back. Krishna (the Absolute) is the Sun. When the mind is placed in the orbit of the Sun ('mat-paraḥ'), the gravitational pull of the sensory planets is rendered mathematically irrelevant.",
