            text: "Rationally, a system is fragile if it requires constant external inputs to maintain equilibrium. The Yogi has engineered a perfectly closed-loop psychological system. By routing the source of 'satisfaction' entirely internally to the infinite consciousness (Nitya-tṛpto), the system requires zero external variables to maintain perfect homeostasis. It is a biologically and psychologically anti-fragile system.",
