            text: "Vedanta distinguishes between 'Sanchita' (accumulated karma) and 'Prarabdha' (the karma already set in motion for this specific life). The fire of knowledge burns the accumulated mountain, ensuring no *future* rebirths. However, the arrow already shot from the bow (Prarabdha) must still land. If you committed a crime, you will go to jail. But you will go to jail as a free, awakened soul, unaffected by the suffering of the cell.",
