          text: "If you have ever tried to build a new habit (waking up at 5 AM, eating clean, meditating) and completely failed by day three, you are living Verse 33. The 'Yoga' sounded great on paper, but the 'Cañcalatvāt' (restlessness) of your mind shattered it. Arjuna gives voice to the exhaustion of trying to be perfect.",
