            title: "Protocol Adherence",
            text: "Rationally, to achieve a highly improbable state (like nuclear fusion or spiritual liberation), the parameters of the experiment must be strictly controlled ('vaśyātmanā'). Random, chaotic inputs ('asaṃyatātmanā') mathematically guarantee the failure of the reaction. 'Upāyataḥ' represents strict protocol adherence. By executing the proper algorithm, the improbable state becomes a reproducible, guaranteed output.",
