          text: "Modern life is defined by an exhausting, restless chase—chasing a better house ('nivāsa'), a better partner/friend ('suhṛt'), or a promotion ('gati'). We are constantly running on a treadmill of desires. Verse 18 is the ultimate 'stop' sign. It says: Everything you are frantically running around the world trying to find is already residing within you as the Supreme.",
