      literal:
        "The Supreme Lord initiates a new phase of instruction. He addresses Arjuna as 'mahā-bāho' (mighty-armed) and commands him: 'bhūya eva śṛṇu' (listen once again) to My supreme, ultimate instruction (me paramaṃ vacaḥ). Krishna explicitly states His motivation for continuing: 'Because you are taking great pleasure in hearing Me and are very dear to Me (prīyamāṇāya), I will speak to you (vakṣyāmi) purely out of a desire for your ultimate welfare and benefit (hita-kāmyayā).'",
