            text: "Psychologically, the human ego loves to say, 'I already know this. I've heard it before.' This creates a cognitive block. By commanding Arjuna to 'listen again', Krishna demands the beginner's mind. Growth requires shedding the arrogance of past knowledge and becoming a thirsty, empty cup once more.",
