            text: "Arjuna did not fail; he graduated. He saw the Universal Form, understood the absolute mechanics of reality, and then consciously realized that pure, loving devotion to the personal form of Bhagavan is superior to staring at cosmic mechanics. The rejection of the Universal Form is the ultimate victory of Bhakti (devotion) over Jnana (knowledge).",
